headline: UPS cancels deal for Estafeta
summary: UPS has dropped its planned purchase of Mexican express delivery company Estafeta because closing conditions were unable to be met. The post UPS cancels deal for Estafeta appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: UPS Terminates Plan to Buy Estafeta
summary: BUSINESS   United Parcel Service terminated its plans to buy Estafeta, abandoning a more than year-long effort to acquire the Mexican small package provider. UPS abandoned the acquisition because not all of the closing conditions could be satisfied, according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission on Thursday.

headline: FedEx Earnings Have Been Disappointing. Where Charts Say Transportation Stocks Go Next
summary: FedEx  has earned a reputation as a serial underperformer when it comes to earnings, with investors frequently disappointed by weak results.  The last five times FedEx reported earnings, the market reacted negatively.  FedEx has been trading in a broad range between the round $200 and $300 levels since last November.
